rComments: The average of the class was 3.86 and we were in total 185 students enrolled so you can do the math of how bad his teaching is. I already studied linear algebra in high school as I was a math major and somehow he managed to make me feel more confused than I was the first time I learned the topics. He keeps skipping between topics.
Worst professor I have ever had! I does not grade or correct assignments He does not care He does not reply to emails

The class itself is very theoretical so it is very hard for students to follow. This prof always goes in detail and mathematically proofs every single thing, that's where student get lost. You should practice the exercises as much as you can to make the abstract ideas a little bit more concrete. So use the textbook.

Guy knows what he's doing... His teaching? It could be more clear, at least from what it is online. Noites are blurry, examples are explained pourly, barely anything is covered in the DGDs. If you want to succeed in this class you better read the manual religiously and find any resources online to learn it yourself if you learn better with examples

This professor makes this class more complicated than it actually is. He has no enthusiasm at all and he goes over the material quickly. The examples he does in class are vague and he doesn't do many of them, so it's a harder to understand the theorems and how to apply them. I'd suggest to avoid him and take the class online during the spring.

This class was a nightmare. The lectures have no structure whatsoever. The questions on the tests are only somewhat reflective of what is taught in class. His handwriting is impossible to read sometimes also.
Worst prof ever. No examples in class, and barely explains. Avoid at all costs.

He is very unwelcoming in his teaching style, as if he doesn't want to be there, and he goes through the material very quickly. His examples tend to be few and far between, and when he does give them, they tend to be vague and confusing.  It's very difficult to gauge what will be included on exams. Go to his office hours, they're somewhat helpful.

N'ACHÈTE PAS de manuel du cours suggéré par la librarie. Je l'ai louée et je le touche même pas pendant le semestre. La meilleure façon d'étudier pour ce cours est pratiquer avec les examens passés, et "Vector Spaces First," un manuel qui est disponibe gratuitement sur BlackBoard. Le style de questions posées sur l'examen ne change jamais.

The class is a difficult one espeially at the biginning. He will introduce the hardest concepts first, making the class more durable as you go on. He will frustrate you at first but you'll learn to appreciate it. My advice is to always refer to practise midterms and exams, those are VERY helpful. Also, his notes in class are very thorough/organized

At First, you'll hate him; Then, once the course really starts, you'll find him an awesome prof, but complicatesssssss a lot of things in the course; then, at the end, you'll find that what you do with him in class + what you do in DGD + The homeworks he gives aren't enough to understand Everything, so his lesson lacks some important details...
Very good professor.
Very good course and the professor made it even better.
The only reason I did well in this class is because I attended all DGDs and read the book religiously. This prof is horrible and doesn't seem to want to HELP the students pass. Not impressed.

This teacher makes the class seem rather hard , although it isn't that complicated. Reading the book was more helpful than i thought especially for Finals.Make sure you do the previous tests, because it gives you a good idea what to expect...

He explains very little, teaching pace is incredibly fast, and he's condescending at times. He isn't very approachable, though he admittedly knows his stuff. Go to the DGDs! I learned most of the stuff there. Classes were torture.
very good
Hard homeworks, he makes everythin more complicated then what it really is
Hard course, but the theacher doesn't help

I felt that he moved a little too fast for me.  His delivery was very dry--that's to be expected for math, but it gave a hard to understand subject even less of an appeal.  I felt he was not approachable with questions.
No Comments
he's a really good teacher but he makes the subject more complicated than it should be... take the class in cegep first, it really helps!!
AWSOME PROF

I think he is a great prof!  I find it unfortunate that many students blame their own lack of motivation/skills/work, on the teacher.  All of his notes are perfectly clear and well formulated.  It is not his responsibility to study and learn for you, he can only present and explain the concepts and then it's up to you, whether you work or not
This class sucked.  D'où...I would chop off my nuts before taking another course with this guy.

Horrible, horrible teacher. Makes absolutely no effort to help visualize, talks solely in mathematical terms, relates no helpful comparisons/analogies, and always seems like he's just trying to get it over with. Doesn't seem to want to teach.       D'où      avoid at all cost!!!

I have to admit that his class is the hardest class to understand.  He's very fast and assumes you know everything as soon as he says it.  You stuggle to write all the notes and you can't listen because all you're doing is writing. Although, it's the subject that sucks, not the prof.  I dont think anyone can make algebra fun. At least he's trying.

Really not a good prof, has no idea how to gauge level of difficulty, his midterms and finals are so long that he can arbitrarily give out whatever marks he wants (since no one finishes). totally plays favorites. (his favorites love him!)
tough guy, sorta makes you feel stupid sometimes because of his high level of understanding. Otherwise, really good teacher. Listen, attend the DGDs and ask smart key questions!!!
hard class with this guy.  fast paced and lots of homework, but a very inspiring individual who encourages his students to try hard.  reasonable, although a bit of a tough marker.

Teaches really fast. His notes are not very clear. You have to try really hard to pass his class. You gotta read the book and attend the DGDs to be succesful. The TAs are often more helpful than he is.
The explanation of theTA are beter than the explanation of the professor
Takes care of students...listen learn and pass
